<li id="cite_note-15"><span class="mw-cite-backlink"><b><a href="#cite_ref-15">^</a></b></span> <span class="reference-text"><cite id="CITEREFBookchin2017" class="citation book cs1"><a href="/wiki/Murray_Bookchin" title="Murray Bookchin">Bookchin, Murray</a> (2 February 2017). <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="https://web.archive.org/web/20211023194646/http://www.revoltlib.com/%3Fid%3D1045"><i>To Remember Spain: The Anarchist and Syndicalist Revolution of 1936</i></a>. Archived from <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.revoltlib.com/?id=1045">the original</a> on 23 October 2021. <q>In anarchist industrial areas like Catalonia, an estimated three-quarters of the economy was placed under workers' control, as it was in anarchist rural areas like Aragon. [...] In the more thoroughly anarchist areas, particularly among the agrarian collectives, money was eliminated and the material means of life were allocated strictly according to need rather than work, following the traditional precepts of a libertarian communist society.</q></cite><span title="ctx_ver=Z39.88-2004&amp;rft_val_fmt=info%3Aofi%2Ffmt%3Akev%3Amtx%3Abook&amp;rft.genre=book&amp;rft.btitle=To+Remember+Spain%3A+The+Anarchist+and+Syndicalist+Revolution+of+1936&amp;rft.date=2017-02-02&amp;rft.aulast=Bookchin&amp;rft.aufirst=Murray&amp;rft_id=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.revoltlib.com%2F%3Fid%3D1045&amp;rfr_id=info%3Asid%2Fen.wikipedia.org%3AAnarchist+communism" class="Z3988"></span></span>
